            <td class="px-4 py-3">KES 500</td>
            <td class="px-4 py-3">10 mins to M-PESA</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td class="px-4 py-3">Bank Transfer</td>
            <td class="px-4 py-3">Banks' rate</td>
            <td class="px-4 py-3">KES 1,000+</td>
            <td class="px-4 py-3">1-3 days</td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-400 mt-2">*Rates and fees are approximate and subject to change</p>
  </div>

  <h2>1. Wise (formerly TransferWise)</h2>
  <p>Best for: Best exchange rates and low fees</p>
  <p>Wise offers the most competitive exchange rates with a small markup (typically 0.5% above the mid-market rate). They charge a transparent fee that's usually lower than traditional banks.</p>
  <p><strong>Key Features:</strong></p>
  <ul>
    <li>Exchange rates close to the real mid-market rate</li>
    <li>Low, transparent fees</li>
    <li>Can send to M-PESA or bank accounts</li>
    <li>Multi-currency account available</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>2. WorldRemit</h2>
  <p>Best for: Fast transfers to M-PESA</p>
  <p>WorldRemit offers instant transfers to M-PESA with competitive rates. They have a user-friendly app and often run promotions for first-time users.</p>
  <p><strong>Key Features:</strong></p>
  <ul>
    <li>Instant transfers to M-PESA</li>
    <li>Competitive exchange rates</li>
    <li>First transfer fee-free offers</li>
    <li>Cash pickup option available</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>3. Remitly</h2>
  <p>Best for: Large transfers with fee-free options</p>
  <p>Remitly offers two transfer speeds: Economy (3-5 days) for lower fees, and Express (minutes) for faster delivery.</p>
  <p><strong>Key Features:</strong></p>
  <ul>
    <li>Fee-free transfers over KES 100,000</li>
    <li>Price match guarantee</li>
    <li>Mobile app with tracking</li>
    <li>Good customer support</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>4. Western Union</h2>
  <p>Best for: Cash pickup locations</p>
  <p>With thousands of agent locations across Kenya, Western Union is a good option for recipients who prefer cash pickup.</p>
  <p><strong>Key Features:</strong></p>
  <ul>
    <li>Wide network of cash pickup locations</li>
    <li>Fast transfers (minutes to hours)</li>
    <li>Mobile wallet deposit option</li>
    <li>24/7 customer service</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>5. Traditional Bank Transfers</h2>
  <p>While convenient, traditional bank transfers are often the most expensive option due to poor exchange rates and high fees.</p>
  <p><strong>Consider banks if:</strong></p>
  <ul>
    <li>You're transferring very large amounts</li>
    <li>Recipient needs funds in their bank account</li>
    <li>You value the security of bank-to-bank transfers</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Tips for Sending Money to Kenya</h2>
  <ol>
    <li><strong>Compare exchange rates</strong> - Small differences can add up, especially for large transfers. Use our <a href="/kes-ugx" class="text-emerald-400 hover:underline">KES to UGX converter</a> if you're also dealing with Ugandan Shillings.</li>
    <li><strong>Watch out for hidden fees</strong> - Some services advertise 'no fees' but make money through poor exchange rates</li>
    <li><strong>Consider transfer speed</strong> - If speed isn't critical, you might get better rates with slower transfer options</li>
    <li><strong>Check for first-time user promotions</strong> - Many services offer fee-free transfers for new customers</li>
    <li><strong>Verify recipient details</strong> - Double-check M-PESA numbers and bank account details</li>
    <li><strong>Check regional rates</strong> - If you're transferring within East Africa, compare <a href="/kes-ugx" class="text-emerald-400 hover:underline">KES to UGX rates</a> for the best deal on cross-border transfers</li>
  </ol>

  <div class="bg-emerald-900 bg-opacity-20 border-l-4 border-emerald-500 p-4 my-6">
    <p class="font-bold text-emerald-300 mb-2">Pro Tip:</p>
    <p>For amounts over KES 100,000, consider splitting your transfer to take advantage of fee-free tiers that many services offer for first-time or large transfers.</p>
  </div>

  <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
  
  <h3>What's the cheapest way to send money to Kenya?</h3>
  <p>Wise typically offers the best combination of low fees and good exchange rates for most transfer amounts. For transfers over KES 100,000, Remitly's fee-free option can be the most cost-effective.</p>
  
  <h3>How can I send money to M-PESA from abroad?</h3>
  <p>Services like WorldRemit, Remitly, and Western Union allow direct transfers to M-PESA. The recipient receives an SMS with instructions to withdraw the money or it's deposited directly into their M-PESA account.</p>
  
  <h3>Are there limits on how much I can send to Kenya?</h3>
  <p>Yes, most services have limits that vary by verification level. Typically, you can send up to KES 1,000,000 per transfer with full verification. M-PESA has a daily limit of KES 150,000 for most users.</p>
  
  <h3>How long do international transfers to Kenya take?</h3>
  <p>Transfers to M-PESA are usually instant or take a few minutes. Bank transfers typically take 1-3 business days. Times can vary based on the service used and the time of day the transfer is initiated.</p>

  <h3>What about transfers between Kenya and Uganda?</h3>
  <p>For transfers between Kenya and Uganda, consider using our <a href="/kes-ugx" class="text-emerald-400 hover:underline">KES to UGX converter</a> to check live exchange rates. Many East African mobile money services offer direct transfers between M-PESA (Kenya) and MTN Mobile Money (Uganda) with competitive rates.</p>
  
